    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-13T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-13T08:00:00-05:00" n="44"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.7962/52: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jacobs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-13T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 13, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 4:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1602. With reference to telegram 1551, June 8, 11 a.m., Legation is informed that
                    no decision on airport project was adopted by Council of Ministers but that it
                    will be discussed at another subsequent meeting. Contacted Commercial
                        Counselor<note n="2" xml:id="d44fn2">Charles Empson.</note> of the British
                    Embassy who has promised to furnish further information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jacobs</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
